data-triple-N3.o: "The Austrian Empire (Austrian German: Kaiserthum Oesterreich, modern spelling Kaisertum Osterreich) was a modern era successor empire centered on what is today's Austria and which officially lasted from 1804 to 1867. It was followed by the Empire of Austria-Hungary, whose proclamation was a diplomatic move that elevated Hungary's status within the Austrian Empire as a result of the Austro-Hungarian Compromise of 1867."@en
